content:
A time combo chart shows two or more measures over time. You can display each measure as a line or bar on the same or separate axes.

Use a time combo chart to analyze two or more measures over time, such as total opportunity amount and number of opportunities.

In the lens:

* Click  and select Time Combo chart type.
* In Time Axis, select date field and granularity.
* In Y-Axis, choose at least two measures.
* First measure displays on time bar graph, subsequent measures display on timeline graph.

To change chart display:

* Click  and set chart properties in Formatting panel.
* Add reference line to provide visual cue about a particular point in time.
* Specify date in Time for reference line.
* Choose label and color for reference line.
title: Time Combo Charts in Salesforce Analytics
